  "prompt": "What does the Tagalog word \"salamat\" mean in English?",
  "response": "The Tagalog word **\"salamat\"** translates to **\"thank you\"** in English. It is commonly used to express gratitude in various situations. For example:\n\n- **Salamat po.**  \n  *(Thank you, sir/madam.)* \u2014 A more formal way to say thank you.\n\n- **Maraming salamat.**  \n  *(Thank you very much.)*\n\n**Usage Example:**\n\n- **Person A:** \"Here is your coffee.\"  \n- **Person B:** \"Salamat!\"\n\nFeel free to use \"salamat\" in everyday conversations to show appreciation!",
